# HTML CSS to IMG API Plugin Documentation

## 1. Overview

The **HTML CSS to IMG API Plugin** allows integration with the HTML CSS to IMG service, enabling users to convert HTML and CSS code into an image. 

## 2. Configuration

Sign in into [HCTI](https://htmlcsstoimage.com/).

Go to API Key in navigator and check Your API key. 

![API key]()

Install HTML CSS to IMAGE plugin in NoCode-X hub. Create data based on data-format:

![creating data]()

Your data should look like:

![data]()

## 3. Available Methods

### 1. **HTML & CSS to Image: Convert Code to an Image**

- **Description:** This action calls the API [Convert HTML & CSS to Image](https://api.htmlcsstoimg.com) to generate an image from a provided block of HTML and CSS code.

#### How to Use  
1. **Prepare action in Your logic:**  
   Include the `html` and `css` code that you want to convert into an image in the request body.

**Logic Example:**  
![LOGIC]()

2. **Result:**  
   The **RESPONSE** will contain the URL or base64-encoded data of the generated image.

#### Expected Response  
- Returns the generated image URL or image data in the specified format.

**Response Example:**  
![RESPONSE]()



